id: pm-bu50
title: pm-changelog extension fails on large tracker JSON
description: "The installed pm-changelog package command fails in this repository because its extension handler shells out to pm list-all --json with Node's default spawnSync buffer. This repository emits about 5.4 MB of JSON, triggering ENOBUFS before changelog generation can run."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: bug,changelog,package,upstream
created_at: "2026-05-23T20:27:39.801Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T21:21:43.846Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog
parent: pm-7811
severity: high
environment: pm-cli repository with 5.4 MB pm list-all --json output
repro_steps: "Install pm-changelog 2026.5.23-1 with pm install npm:pm-changelog --project, then run pm changelog generate --stdout --status closed --group-by version."
expected_result: The extension command generates changelog output or uses a streaming/input path for large trackers.
actual_result: Command fails with extension_command_handler_failed; direct spawnSync reproduction reports spawnSync pm ENOBUFS.
affected_version: 2026.5.23-1
component: pm-changelog
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-23T20:44:08.277Z",codex-pm-changelog,"Upstream status: fixed in unbraind/pm-changelog commit 5c83152 with green GitHub CI run 26343027144. npm publish of 2026.5.23-2 is blocked by npm 2FA from this shell, so pm-cli installs the fixed package from GitHub main commit 5c83152 for now."
  "2026-05-23T21:21:34.924Z",codex-pm-changelog-integrator,"Evidence: fixed upstream in pm-changelog 2026.5.23-5 at f5ebc23c7e3dbc9d41ac687b14826fe5632e9d1a. GitHub Actions run 26343824903 passed, issue unbraind/pm-changelog#1 is closed, and pm-cli package doctor plus pnpm changelog:pm:check pass with this package installed from GitHub. npm publication remains blocked by npm E403 2FA/bypass-token requirements, but the functional defect is resolved in source and in this repo."
close_reason: "Resolved upstream and verified in pm-cli via installed pm-changelog 2026.5.23-5; npm publication is an external authorization blocker, not an unfixed package defect."
body: ""
